#banprivatejets:
the social debate

THE PROJECT

In 2022 private jets have become a relevant topic in the fight against climate change. Using #banprivatejets, groups of activists, politicians and scientists have begun to highlight the need to tax emissions of private jets more decisively or, more extremely, to ban them. The project has been carried out during the Final Synthesis Design Studio held by DensityDesign of the MSc in Communication Design, Politecnico di Milano. This web project is part of previous research published in a report.

Pollution
"Oh my, the Jets are polluting everything."
This topic collects all the comments containing words related to pollution caused by the use of private jets (CO2 emissions in particular) and to environmental issues in general. It is common in these comments to see people compare jet pollution with other pollution problems and sources.
Turtles
The word turtles is very recurring in this topic and unexpected. Many people write things like â€œwhat will turtles doâ€ referring to the fact that they have often been taken as an example of victims of pollution and climate change.

Flight routine
"My friend has a friend who is a private jet pilot."
Here are all the words related to the routine of a private jet: people involved, procedures and also differences with regular scheduled flights. These comments are mainly about explanations or technical questions about the flight routine of aircrafts and are characterized by technical terminology and informative tone of voice.

Celebrities
"A 3-minute flight?
Their time is money."
This group of keywords collects peopleâ€™s names and places related to news and debates that criticize a specific celebrity and their usage of private flights. In this case, comments are divided between fans of these celebrities (particularly the Kardashian family) and haters of this approach whereby they take private flights even for very few minutes.
Ventura
Many comments in this topic are related to the debate around Ventura County, referring to Kylie Jenner that used her private jet just to land in Camarillo, close to her makeup factory in Oxnard, for a flight of just 12 minutes. Another name that is often mentioned is Drake, considered to be among the main users of private jets in the world.

Everyday life
"Enough! I am going back to plastic straws."
People denounce private jet users for their disregard for the environment and reflect on the fact that they, doing small good deeds daily, can do nothing by comparison and feel that they are performing unnecessary actions compared to the massive CO2 emissions of the jets.
Straws
When talking about the actions and problems of daily life many people mention straws since plastic ones have recently been banned. People therefore think that being punished for the occasional use of a plastic straw is an injustice when other people pollute so much on their own.
